tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glucose control and possible prediabetes or diabetes. All other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, and calcium, are within normal limits except for slightly low creatinine, which may reflect reduced muscle mass in elderly patients and is not clinically concerning. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
